Your Honor,

I stand before you today, taking full responsibility for my actions. I plea guilty to the offense of speeding.

On the day of the incident, I was driving my brand-new car and in my excitement, I exceeded the speed limit. I must admit that my fascination with testing the car's speed got the best of me. I now realize the danger I imposed on those around me, and I deeply regret my actions.

Furthermore, I failed to respond to the notice of intended prosecution (NIP) as I neglected to regularly check my mail. If I had been aware of it, I would have promptly responded and taken appropriate measures. I understand that my failure to check my mail is no excuse for not abiding by the law.

I also want to bring to your attention that I am 26 years old and already have penalty points on my license from three previous incidents of speeding. However, apart from these driving offenses, I have no criminal record. Additionally, I have been diagnosed with ADHD, which may have contributed to my impulsive behavior on that particular day. I understand that this is not an excuse, but I wanted to provide some context to my actions.

In conclusion, I stand before you today, fully acknowledging my guilt and prepared to face the consequences for my actions. I ask for your consideration in determining a fair penalty, taking into account the circumstances of my case. I assure you that I am committed to rectifying my behavior and becoming a law-abiding citizen.

Thank you for your attention.
